Description: Practical improv training for business
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Improvisation is a skill practiced by everyone, every single day. At Oak and Reeds, our definition of "improv" is the practice of unplanned interaction with others.  As much as we would like to rehearse and practice our lines for critical moments, there's no script sitting on our desk each morning, outlining all the things we'll say and do throughout the day. We work with each client to determine exactly which skills they seek to develop. We then guide the client's team through custom, improv-based workshops with activities picked to hone the desired skills. After each engagement, we leave participants with a development plan for how they can continue to practice the new skills. These plans can then be folded into ongoing learning and development strategies.

Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Evirx develops technologies for evidence-informed decision making.  Evirx has a specialty in developing technologies that capture evidence of people demonstrating skills, knowledge, and competencies in the field and allowing supervisors to assess and provide feedback. The Video Analysis Tool (VAT) is their first such tool. VAT captures video in remote locations, allows users to upload from anywhere they have an Internet connection, and then allows a supervisor or instructor to assess to what extent the person demonstrates competencies to set standards. All of this is done through an intuitive web interface.  Evirx technologies have applications in every sector where training, teaching, and learning are taking place including healthcare, medicine, education, military, and corporate training. It's approach to decision making tools is to help organizations utilize the most powerful evidence to explain the extent to which someone has demonstrated a competency or expected outcome. Information generated informs decisions about future training, growth and development of employees/learners,  progress toward set standards, and ROI on existing training efforts.

Description: AOC is a company that exhibits a knack for multi-cultural diversity by selling welding gases and other compressed gases.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Acetylene Oxygen Company manufactures and distributes industrial, medical, and specialty gases in Texas and Mexico. It offers high pressure cylinder gases, including air, argon, carbon dioxide, helium, hydrogen, nitrogen, oxygen, and propane; and low pressure cylinder gases, such as acetylene.  The company also bulk gases, including argon, carbon dioxide, nitrogen, oxygen; chlorine, sulfur dioxide, and anhydrous for water treatment; and medical gases, such as oxygen, carbon dioxide, nitrogen, and nitrous oxide. In addition, Acetylene Oxygen Company packages chlorine, caustic soda, SO2, and anhydrous ammonia from railcars to cylinders; and distributes to the water treatment industry. Further, the company distributes welding and safety supplies, including gas apparatus, welding machines, plasma products, power and hand tools, safety equipment, hand tools, welding accessories, and pool chemicals. Acetylene Oxygen Company was founded in 1936 and is based in Harlingen, Texas.  As of November 16, 2012, Acetylene Oxygen Company operates as a subsidiary of Praxair Distribution, Inc.
